The Xiaomi Corporation has announced yesterday that the much-anticipated Redmi Note 11 series will launch in Nigeria on Wednesday. As a hugely popular product series with over 240 million units sold worldwide, Redmi Note Series gives Nigerians affordable device. This series of mid-range devices is set to offer superior specs in the realms of camera, display, battery and charging efficiency, providing high-level performance to suit the ever-evolving needs of consumers across the board. A statement by the phone maker said Redmi Note 11 Series is the next step in Xiaomi’s global mandate to make innovative technology both accessible and affordable. “Introducing the Redmi Note 11 Series is just the beginning of Xiaomi’s 2022 objective to satisfy Xiaomi fans’ appetite for cutting-edge technology and further elevate user experiences’’, the statement said As the year progresses, the company is set to release smartphones and AIoT technologies that enables Nigerians to maximise their lifestyles and make the most of every moment. Xiaomi has been in the Nigerian market since 2019. Xiaomi is actively expanding its networks through mobile operators and online distributors to increase the availability of their devices at multiple touchpoints.